FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1774857950
OL,3,CNASA's Artemis II astronauts arrive at
OL,4,CFlorida launch site for moon trip
OL,6,FShe said: "We have the opportunity to
OL,7,Fsee parts of the far side of the moon
OL,8,Fwith human eyes that have never been
OL,9,Fseen before.
OL,11,F"I am so grateful to those that paved
OL,12,Fthe way for me to be here and for all
OL,13,Fof us to be here. And it's an honour
OL,14,Fto potentially inspire the explorers
OL,15,Fof the future. But again, the big
OL,16,Fthing to celebrate is we collectively
OL,17,Fmade the decision to be here."
OL,19,FCommander Reid Wiseman said: "The
OL,20,Frocket is ready. We are ready. NASA is
OL,21,Fready.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
